			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>I&#8217;ve been on a roll lately and haven&#8217;t had the time for the blog that I would like.  But then, from the total lack of comments I get and noticing in my stat program that most of the hits I do get are coming from spammers, I suppose it doesn&#8217;t make much difference how frequently or infrequently I update this thing.  I do love my spam killer, though.  Nothing gets through.</p>
<p>Anyway, I finished my story <em>The Karaoke Singer</em> for the latest Backspace contest on the day it was due.  There were a number of better stories but it still came in at the 4th or 5th position.  Not bad for a story I wrote and edited in a day.  As much as I enjoy entering the contests and certainly winning is a real ego boost, I have to say it&#8217;s mixed blessing.  I really hate coming up with the parameters for the next contest.  I&#8217;m much more comfortable writing to someone else&#8217;s parameters.</p>
<p>I polished the story up, made a few changes and sent it out.  I also pulled a few other stories out of the bin, some that were ready to go and some that needed work, did what needed to be done and sent them out as well.  I&#8217;ve got one story, <em>Fire and Slush</em> that I&#8217;m looking for a market for.  It&#8217;s going to be tough sell as it&#8217;s really a writers story but I&#8217;ll keep trying.</p>
<p>In any event, the following stories are out and about: <em>The Karaoke Singer, Final Target, The Dance</em> and <em>Plugging The Pooch</em>.  Wish me luck.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
